I scan 1686/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Thanh Hóa) and 1687/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Vĩnh Long), but the "Long Định" references are in different provinces.

Based on this analysis, specifically Resolution 1682/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Tây Ninh), my best assessment is that the original address "Xã Long Định, Huyện Cần Đước, Tỉnh Long An" is now "part of" the new ward "Xã Long Cang". This is the most logical transformation I can infer from the available data.
